## Inheritance Rules & Behavior

**What Happens When Parent Updates:**

**Scenario 1: Parent adds new component**
```
Parent (PlayerCharacter):
├── Add new component: "StaminaComponent"
└── Save

System Action:
└── Automatically adds "StaminaComponent" to ALL children:
    ├── WarriorCharacter: + StaminaComponent (inherited)
    ├── MageCharacter: + StaminaComponent (inherited)
    └── ArcherCharacter: + StaminaComponent (inherited)
```

**Scenario 2: Parent changes variable default value**
```
Parent (PlayerCharacter):
├── Change: maxHealth = 100.0 → 120.0
└── Save

System Action:
├── WarriorCharacter:
│   └── maxHealth = 150.0 (overridden, UNCHANGED)
├── MageCharacter:
│   └── maxHealth = 120.0 (inherited, UPDATED)
└── ArcherCharacter:
    └── maxHealth = 120.0 (inherited, UPDATED)

Rule: Children with overrides keep their values
      Children without overrides get new parent value
```

**Scenario 3: Parent removes component**
```
Parent (PlayerCharacter):
├── Remove: "HealthComponent"
└── Save

System Action:
└── Removes "HealthComponent" from ALL children:
    ├── WarriorCharacter: - HealthComponent
    ├── MageCharacter: - HealthComponent
    └── ArcherCharacter: - HealthComponent

⚠️ Warning shown: "This will remove HealthComponent from 3 child classes"
```

**Scenario 4: Parent modifies blueprint logic**
```
Parent (PlayerCharacter):
├── Modify: OnBeginPlay node graph
└── Save

System Action:
├── WarriorCharacter:
│   └── OnBeginPlay: Custom logic (overridden, UNCHANGED)
├── MageCharacter:
│   └── OnBeginPlay: Updated to new parent logic
└── ArcherCharacter:
    └── OnBeginPlay: Updated to new parent logic
```

