## Propagation System (Parent → Children Updates)

**Update Propagation Flow:**
```
1. User saves parent class
   ↓
2. System detects changes:
   - New components
   - Removed components
   - Modified default values
   - Blueprint changes
   ↓
3. For each child class:
   ├── Load child class
   ├── Check for overrides
   ├── Apply non-overridden changes
   ├── Keep overridden values
   ├── Validate integrity
   └── Save child class
   ↓
4. Show summary:
   "Updated 3 child classes successfully"
```

**Propagation Rules Table:**
```
| Change Type          | Child w/o Override | Child w/ Override |
|----------------------|-------------------|-------------------|
| Add component        | ✓ Added           | ✓ Added           |
| Remove component     | ✓ Removed         | ✓ Removed         |
| Add variable         | ✓ Added           | ✓ Added           |
| Remove variable      | ✓ Removed         | ✓ Removed         |
| Change default value | ✓ Updated         | ✗ Keep override   |
| Modify blueprint     | ✓ Updated         | ✗ Keep override   |
| Add node             | ✓ Added           | ✓ Added           |
| Remove node          | ✓ Removed         | ✓ Removed*        |

* Warning shown if child references removed node
```

