## Instance vs Class

**Important Distinction:**
```
CLASS (Blueprint/Template):
├── Defines structure and default values
├── Stored in Content Browser
├── Can be parent or child
└── Changes affect all instances

INSTANCE (Spawned in Scene):
├── Created from a class
├── Placed in scene
├── Can override class values
└── Changes only affect this instance

Example:
├── Class: WarriorCharacter (in Content Browser)
│   └── Default health: 150
│
└── Instances in Scene:
    ├── Warrior_01 (health: 150 from class)
    ├── Warrior_02 (health: 200 overridden in instance)
    └── Warrior_03 (health: 150 from class)

