The Point (Like Unreal Engine Inheritance)
Class Inheritance System:

Create parent classes as templates
Create child classes that inherit everything
Children can override parent values (but structure stays)
Children can add new components/variables/logic
Parent updates propagate to all children automatically
Overrides are preserved during propagation
Right-click to create child in Content Browser

Key Features:

Visual inheritance indicators (🔗 inherited, ✏️ overridden, ➕ added)
Override system with reset capability
Warning system for parent modifications
Class hierarchy browser
Version tracking and sync
Propagation with conflict resolution

Use Cases:

Enemy types (Enemy → Zombie, Skeleton, Boss)
Character classes (Player → Warrior, Mage, Archer)
Item types (Item → Weapon → Sword, Axe, Bow)
Vehicle variants (Vehicle → Car → SportsCar, Truck)

Integration Requirements:

Must work with existing Actor system
Must work with Component system
Must work with Variables and Structures
Must work with Blueprint/Node editor
Must save inheritance data to JSON
Must work with Content Browser
Must work with project save/load system
Propagation must be automatic and safe

Benefits:

DRY principle (Don't Repeat Yourself)
Easy to maintain (change parent, update all children)
Clear hierarchy and organization
Override system for customization
Exactly like Unreal Engine
Professional class architecture
